\begin_layout Subsection
Architecture of the project
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Firmware and data flow
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The firmware (main.ino) is a basic C++ code uploaded to the nodeMCU that
 get the data from the DHT sensor and send it through a http get request
 to the server (app.py), the server then manage the request and save the
 data into the database file data.db and the log file log.txt.
 Finnally, the web browser display the data with the index.html page (cf
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Frontend"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Variables :
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is 5 variables to change in this program to make it works :
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
DHTPIN : the nodeMUC pin connected to the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

data
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 pin, I used GPIO 5 (cf 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Connections"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
ssid : ssid of the internet network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
password : password of the internet network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
serverIP : IP adress of the machine that will run the server.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
serverPort : port chosen when creating the server, 5000 here.
\end_layout

