\begin_layout Subsection
Features
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Running capture
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After starting it, app will show the data currently in the database, including
 potential previous data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To start a new capture (clear the existing data if you want), click on 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

open
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 to initialize the system (actually not really working like this, since
 the nodeMCU send data without knowing if anything receive it), then click
 on 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

start
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 to start the capture (wont work if system is closed).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Same as start/open, you can stop the capture and close the system with the
 corresponding buttons.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Clear data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Click on the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Clear data
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 button if you want to clear all the visualizations, the data will be lost
 if not saved with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Save Log
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 beforehand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Set capture interval
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Set the capture interval (in s) that you want, either using the arrows to
 increase/decrease it or by writing it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It should work well with intervals 
\begin_inset Formula $\geq3s$
\end_inset

, but since the nodeMCU takes some times to execute its capture loop, the
 actual interval might be longer for 1 and 2 seconds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Save log
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You can save the current data using the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Save Log
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 button, saved data will be stored in ~/server/data/saves in the project
 repository.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Load log
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You can load data from a log using the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Load Log
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

