\begin_layout Subsection
Incident
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When trying to the upload this code on the nodeMCU, it crashed and even
 after repluging it, the usb port was not detected by arduinoIDE.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After I reseted the nodeMCU using the flash button, the usb port appeared
 again, but there was an error each times I tried to upload a code to the
 nodeMCU afterward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The crash was apparently caused by a buffer overflow present in the code
 that I pasted from the instructions :
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

long rssi = WiFi.RSSI();
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

char buffer[3];
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

char* strptr = ltoa(rssi, buffer, 10);
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

